The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Trucks crush cop, wife
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Trucks crush cop, wife
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	A traffic constable and his wife were crushed between two trucks early on Monday.        
	Shyamal Kumar Ray, 42, and wife Anjali, 35, were on a motorcycle when the mishap occurred at the Raja Dinendra Street-Aurobindo Sarani crossing.         
	Bimalesh Kumar, the helper of one of the trucks, was killed, too.        
	The couple had left home on their motorcycle at 4.40am and were headed to the morning haat near Khanna cinema crossing on APC Road.        
	The bodies were crushed and there was blood everywhere. Glass shards were strewn all over, said S. Mishra, the security guard of an ATM at the crossing.                                                                                                                                                                         
